resources

Here is a list of things which I find useful and intend to find useful in the future. A lot of these are video links as I somehow learn faster from them. Included at the bottom is also a list of books which I like, followed by a list of people I find interesting and tend to look up to. I am by no means an expert in any of these fields, so if you have any suggestions, let me know!


Learning Resources

  • Control Bootcamp

Kalman Filters

  • ilectureonline by Michel van Biezen. How the whole concept first clicked in my head.
  • Matlab tutorials.
  • SLAM course - WS13/14 by Prof. Cyrill Stachniss, University of Bonn. Literal gold.

Machine Learning

  • Machine Learning by Andrew Ng, Stanford University.

Math

  • Algebra, Topology, Differential Calculus, and Optimization Theory For Computer Science and Machine Learning by UPenn. Basically a math dictionary for engineering or computer science.
